[SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:01:48.650 --> 00:01:49.820
[SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:03:22.490 --> 00:03:24.580
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:03:24.580 --> 00:03:27.260
INTERPRETER: So
regardless of topic,

00:03:27.260 --> 00:03:29.117
let's just engage in a dialogue.

00:03:29.117 --> 00:03:30.450
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:03:30.450 --> 00:03:31.408
INTERPRETER: It's good?

00:03:42.130 --> 00:03:44.201
MALE SPEAKER:
Afternoon, my friends.

00:03:44.201 --> 00:03:48.030
Pomnyun Sunim is
no ordinary monk.

00:03:48.030 --> 00:03:50.440
He's the winner of
the Magsaysay Award,

00:03:50.440 --> 00:03:53.140
which is Asia's
Nobel Peace Prize.

00:03:53.140 --> 00:03:55.600
He was one of the
very first people

00:03:55.600 --> 00:03:59.590
to organize food aid for
North Korea back in the 1990s.

00:03:59.590 --> 00:04:02.480
Yeah, back when
even I was young.

00:04:02.480 --> 00:04:04.830
His deep engagement
with North Koreans

00:04:04.830 --> 00:04:09.380
have made him one of the world's
top experts on North Korea.

00:04:09.380 --> 00:04:14.700
He is a popular zen teacher
and he's a widely respected

00:04:14.700 --> 00:04:17.519
international
humanitarian leader.

00:04:17.519 --> 00:04:21.769
Venerable Pomnyun
Sunim is the chairman

00:04:21.769 --> 00:04:23.970
of the Peace
Foundation in Seoul,

00:04:23.970 --> 00:04:28.740
which supports policy
research and analysis aimed

00:04:28.740 --> 00:04:34.070
at Korean unification--
peaceful unification--

00:04:34.070 --> 00:04:37.250
and humanitarian
issues in North Korea.

00:04:37.250 --> 00:04:42.040
He is also a Zen master with
the Seoul-based Jungto Society,

00:04:42.040 --> 00:04:46.990
which he originally established
in 1988 to facilitate self

00:04:46.990 --> 00:04:49.560
improvement through
volunteerism.

00:04:49.560 --> 00:04:52.112
And overall, he's
just a cool dude.

00:04:52.112 --> 00:04:54.570
And my friends, please welcome
the Venerable Pomnyun Sunim.

00:04:59.579 --> 00:05:01.420
Sunim, thank you so
much for being here.

00:05:01.420 --> 00:05:04.870
We're so honored to have you.

00:05:04.870 --> 00:05:06.287
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:06.287 --> 00:05:08.495
INTERPRETER: Thank you for
inviting me to this event.

00:05:08.495 --> 00:05:10.270
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:10.270 --> 00:05:12.417
INTERPRETER: And it's
great to see you all today.

00:05:12.417 --> 00:05:13.750
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:13.750 --> 00:05:15.460
INTERPRETER: You
must be all busy.

00:05:15.460 --> 00:05:17.502
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:17.502 --> 00:05:19.710
INTERPRETER: So is it OK
for you to be here and waste

00:05:19.710 --> 00:05:20.543
your time like this?

00:05:20.543 --> 00:05:22.230
[LAUGHTER]

00:05:22.230 --> 00:05:25.990
MALE SPEAKER: They
get paid to sit here.

00:05:25.990 --> 00:05:27.377
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:27.377 --> 00:05:29.335
INTERPRETER: So they
don't have to do anything.

00:05:29.335 --> 00:05:30.200
You still pay them?

00:05:30.200 --> 00:05:30.550
MALE SPEAKER: Yes.

00:05:30.550 --> 00:05:32.234
Well, I get paid
to sit with you.

00:05:32.234 --> 00:05:35.900
[LAUGHTER]

00:05:35.900 --> 00:05:39.259
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:39.259 --> 00:05:41.050
INTERPRETER: So I think
I need to thank you

00:05:41.050 --> 00:05:42.720
all first here at Google.

00:05:42.720 --> 00:05:45.610
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:45.610 --> 00:05:48.080
INTERPRETER: Because of you,
I derive a lot of benefits.

00:05:48.080 --> 00:05:50.450
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:52.450
INTERPRETER: I travel
all over the world.

00:05:52.450 --> 00:05:54.112
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:05:54.112 --> 00:05:56.570
INTERPRETER: So I especially
travel to those areas that are

00:05:56.570 --> 00:05:57.780
less travelled.

00:05:57.780 --> 00:06:02.345
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:02.345 --> 00:06:05.090
INTERPRETER: Because you allow
a free use of the Google Maps,

00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:06.720
I tend to use it very often.

00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:07.820
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:09.153
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:09.153 --> 00:06:10.250
INTERPRETER: Thank you.

00:06:10.250 --> 00:06:11.710
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:11.710 --> 00:06:13.850
INTERPRETER: But there is
also not so good things.

00:06:13.850 --> 00:06:17.670
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:17.670 --> 00:06:19.170
INTERPRETER: Because
I travel often,

00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:21.450
I should know my way
around fairly well.

00:06:21.450 --> 00:06:23.610
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:23.610 --> 00:06:25.860
INTERPRETER: So I should
know every nooks and crannies

00:06:25.860 --> 00:06:26.590
in Seoul.

00:06:26.590 --> 00:06:33.850
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:33.850 --> 00:06:37.190
INTERPRETER: So if I were
to quit from being a monk,

00:06:37.190 --> 00:06:39.810
I would have been made
an excellent taxi driver.

00:06:39.810 --> 00:06:41.911
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:41.911 --> 00:06:44.160
INTERPRETER: But right now,
my talents are now wasted.

00:06:44.160 --> 00:06:45.820
It's useless anymore.

00:06:45.820 --> 00:06:50.639
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:50.639 --> 00:06:52.180
INTERPRETER: Because
the GPS actually

00:06:52.180 --> 00:06:56.087
knows the roads a
lot better than I do.

00:06:56.087 --> 00:06:57.420
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:06:57.420 --> 00:06:59.797
INTERPRETER: So another
matter to thank you about--

00:06:59.797 --> 00:07:01.130
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:07:01.130 --> 00:07:02.330
INTERPRETER: --is YouTube.

00:07:02.330 --> 00:07:12.540
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:07:12.540 --> 00:07:15.770
INTERPRETER: So my dialogues,
engagement with folks,

00:07:15.770 --> 00:07:18.020
the video clips of those
are on the YouTube.

00:07:18.020 --> 00:07:20.050
And that allows
Koreans communities

00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:24.000
across the world to be able
to speak with me vicariously.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:26.740
And that made it easy for
me to engage with them.

00:07:26.740 --> 00:07:33.272
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:07:33.272 --> 00:07:34.730
INTERPRETER: Before,
our engagement

00:07:34.730 --> 00:07:38.560
was limited by time and space
and limited to areas like this,

00:07:38.560 --> 00:07:39.390
spaces like this.

00:07:39.390 --> 00:07:44.450
But now our engagement has been
freed from that limitation.

00:07:44.450 --> 00:07:45.920
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:07:45.920 --> 00:07:47.637
INTERPRETER: And
this is also free.

00:07:47.637 --> 00:07:48.970
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:52.720
INTERPRETER: So thank
you doubly for that.

00:07:52.720 --> 00:07:54.860
MALE SPEAKER: So Sunim,
I am aware that you're

00:07:54.860 --> 00:07:56.590
on a world tour.

00:07:56.590 --> 00:08:00.850
You are touring, you're
giving 115 lectures

00:08:00.850 --> 00:08:05.060
in 115 cities in 115 days.

00:08:05.060 --> 00:08:09.580
And Mountain View is
lecture number 79.

00:08:09.580 --> 00:08:12.320
And tonight you're
going to Oakland,

00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:15.530
and they'll be lecture 80.

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:17.590
Young people like
him, lots of energy.

00:08:17.590 --> 00:08:20.560
Not old people like me.

00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:24.090
So, my dear friend, your
world tour-- what do you

00:08:24.090 --> 00:08:25.800
hope to achieve in doing this?

00:08:29.295 --> 00:08:31.240
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:08:31.240 --> 00:08:35.159
INTERPRETER: There's no specific
thing I'm trying to achieve.

00:08:35.159 --> 00:08:37.480
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:08:37.480 --> 00:08:40.127
INTERPRETER: So a lot of people
suffer in their everyday lives.

00:08:40.127 --> 00:08:41.460
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:08:41.460 --> 00:08:42.419
INTERPRETER: To listen to them--

00:08:42.419 --> 00:08:43.679
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:08:43.679 --> 00:08:45.304
INTERPRETER: --and
to engage with them.

00:08:45.304 --> 00:08:50.710
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:08:50.710 --> 00:08:52.260
INTERPRETER: And
I feel fulfilled

00:08:52.260 --> 00:08:54.690
when I see their
suffering alleviated even

00:08:54.690 --> 00:08:56.140
by a small amount.

00:08:56.140 --> 00:08:58.770
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:08:58.770 --> 00:09:01.210
INTERPRETER: Because they
see me first through YouTube.

00:09:01.210 --> 00:09:02.544
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:02.544 --> 00:09:04.751
INTERPRETER: And they want
to engage with me directly

00:09:04.751 --> 00:09:05.427
in person.

00:09:05.427 --> 00:09:06.760
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:10.040
INTERPRETER: And they also
want to ask questions of me.

00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:11.775
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:11.775 --> 00:09:13.150
INTERPRETER: So
I have been asked

00:09:13.150 --> 00:09:15.320
to come visit them many times.

00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:18.190
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:18.190 --> 00:09:19.940
INTERPRETER: But seeing
how Buddhist monks

00:09:19.940 --> 00:09:24.750
should be fairly not
busy, but I'm always busy.

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:29.461
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:29.461 --> 00:09:31.210
INTERPRETER: So I
didn't have time before,

00:09:31.210 --> 00:09:32.840
but this time I
actually made time

00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:35.330
in order to travel through
the world and meet with them.

00:09:35.330 --> 00:09:43.560
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:43.560 --> 00:09:45.630
INTERPRETER: Second,
because I only speak Korean,

00:09:45.630 --> 00:09:48.800
until now I was able to
engage with Koreans only.

00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:56.677
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:09:56.677 --> 00:09:58.260
INTERPRETER: So if
I were to be reborn

00:09:58.260 --> 00:10:00.000
in the next lifetime
speaking English,

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:02.060
then I'll be able to engage
with English speakers

00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:03.640
and other global
citizens, as well.

00:10:03.640 --> 00:10:06.660
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:10:06.660 --> 00:10:09.960
INTERPRETER: So I'm actually
practicing for my next lifetime

00:10:09.960 --> 00:10:11.420
by doing this world tour.

00:10:11.420 --> 00:10:12.240
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:14.031
INTERPRETER: So it's
an investment, per se.

00:10:16.639 --> 00:10:18.930
MALE SPEAKER: You do recognize
when you get reborn, you

00:10:18.930 --> 00:10:20.600
sort of forget some English?

00:10:25.730 --> 00:10:27.271
He's going, oops.

00:10:27.271 --> 00:10:30.990
[LAUGHTER]

00:10:30.990 --> 00:10:32.486
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:10:32.486 --> 00:10:34.860
INTERPRETER: So no one has
proved that yet, so we'll see.

00:10:37.637 --> 00:10:39.220
MALE SPEAKER: So you
will get a chance

00:10:39.220 --> 00:10:40.940
to ask Sunim some questions.

00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:42.270
We will leave plenty of time.

00:10:42.270 --> 00:10:45.921
So I only have a few
questions, and then we'll

00:10:45.921 --> 00:10:46.920
give you plenty of time.

00:10:49.510 --> 00:10:52.565
So Sunim, I have to ask
you about North Korea

00:10:52.565 --> 00:10:54.440
because you're one of
the world's top experts

00:10:54.440 --> 00:10:55.740
on the topic.

00:10:55.740 --> 00:10:58.790
And I'm just going to ask you
a very broad question, which

00:10:58.790 --> 00:11:02.880
is, talk about peace
and humanitarian issues

00:11:02.880 --> 00:11:04.620
in North Korea today.

00:11:10.816 --> 00:11:19.250
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:19.250 --> 00:11:21.550
INTERPRETER: So when you
say North Korea, images

00:11:21.550 --> 00:11:26.750
of dictatorship, nuclear,
and human rights violations.

00:11:26.750 --> 00:11:28.590
Those are the images
that come to your mind.

00:11:28.590 --> 00:11:32.729
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:32.729 --> 00:11:35.270
INTERPRETER: But we don't often
think that there are actually

00:11:35.270 --> 00:11:38.647
20 million people living there.

00:11:38.647 --> 00:11:39.980
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:39.980 --> 00:11:42.130
INTERPRETER: And they are
suffering as we speak.

00:11:42.130 --> 00:11:43.463
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:43.463 --> 00:11:44.810
INTERPRETER: They lack food.

00:11:44.810 --> 00:11:46.157
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:46.157 --> 00:11:47.490
INTERPRETER: They lack medicine.

00:11:47.490 --> 00:11:48.900
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:50.250
INTERPRETER: They lack water.

00:11:50.250 --> 00:11:51.930
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:51.930 --> 00:11:53.930
INTERPRETER: They lack a
lot of essential goods.

00:11:53.930 --> 00:11:55.080
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:55.080 --> 00:11:56.250
INTERPRETER: They
don't have electricity.

00:11:56.250 --> 00:11:57.760
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:11:57.760 --> 00:11:59.301
INTERPRETER: They
don't have anything

00:11:59.301 --> 00:12:01.160
to burn for heat during winter.

00:12:01.160 --> 00:12:10.134
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:10.134 --> 00:12:11.550
INTERPRETER: Because
we only focus

00:12:11.550 --> 00:12:15.240
on the bad actions
perpetrated by the leadership,

00:12:15.240 --> 00:12:18.350
we forget about the 20 million
people who suffer under them.

00:12:18.350 --> 00:12:24.490
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:24.490 --> 00:12:28.080
INTERPRETER: So I want to focus
on the 20 million people who

00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:31.090
are suffering and think
about their suffering.

00:12:31.090 --> 00:12:35.244
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:35.244 --> 00:12:36.910
INTERPRETER: Because
they have the right

00:12:36.910 --> 00:12:39.590
to ask for help as
part of the human race.

00:12:39.590 --> 00:12:41.470
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:41.470 --> 00:12:43.950
INTERPRETER: And that's
what I seek to do.

00:12:43.950 --> 00:12:48.476
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:48.476 --> 00:12:50.850
INTERPRETER: So many of them,
some of them actually cross

00:12:50.850 --> 00:12:53.877
the river into China because
they cannot suffer anymore.

00:12:53.877 --> 00:12:55.210
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:55.210 --> 00:12:56.668
INTERPRETER: And
they are refugees.

00:12:56.668 --> 00:12:59.644
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:12:59.644 --> 00:13:01.435
INTERPRETER: Of course
China considers them

00:13:01.435 --> 00:13:03.770
as illegal aliens
and repatriates them

00:13:03.770 --> 00:13:05.530
to North Korea.

00:13:05.530 --> 00:13:07.382
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:07.382 --> 00:13:09.340
INTERPRETER: So it's a
little dangerous for you

00:13:09.340 --> 00:13:12.600
to actually actively help
North Korean refugees in China.

00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:15.160
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:15.160 --> 00:13:17.760
INTERPRETER: But they also
have the right to be protected.

00:13:17.760 --> 00:13:20.360
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:20.360 --> 00:13:24.120
INTERPRETER: And so that's why
I give them support when I can.

00:13:24.120 --> 00:13:25.810
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:25.810 --> 00:13:28.590
INTERPRETER: And human rights
is also very bad in North Korea.

00:13:28.590 --> 00:13:31.810
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:31.810 --> 00:13:33.310
INTERPRETER: But
it's very difficult

00:13:33.310 --> 00:13:36.880
to find a way to
alleviate, improve

00:13:36.880 --> 00:13:39.160
that situation in North Korea.

00:13:39.160 --> 00:13:42.020
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:42.020 --> 00:13:45.800
INTERPRETER: But we do have
consistent and constant

00:13:45.800 --> 00:13:47.400
awareness.

00:13:47.400 --> 00:13:50.820
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:50.820 --> 00:13:52.430
INTERPRETER: And
collect information

00:13:52.430 --> 00:13:54.850
about the sufferings and let
the international community

00:13:54.850 --> 00:13:55.890
know about them.

00:13:55.890 --> 00:13:57.314
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:13:57.314 --> 00:13:58.980
INTERPRETER: Because
they have the right

00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:01.680
to live as human beings.

00:14:01.680 --> 00:14:08.970
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:14:08.970 --> 00:14:11.660
INTERPRETER: Not to criticize
the North Korean regime,

00:14:11.660 --> 00:14:13.890
but to give North Korean
people the opportunity

00:14:13.890 --> 00:14:17.330
to live as human beings.

00:14:17.330 --> 00:14:18.950
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:14:18.950 --> 00:14:20.760
INTERPRETER: But this
is not an easy work.

00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:23.580
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:14:23.580 --> 00:14:25.080
INTERPRETER: Because
currently there

00:14:25.080 --> 00:14:28.600
is a great tension between
North and South Korea.

00:14:28.600 --> 00:14:32.390
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:14:32.390 --> 00:14:34.230
INTERPRETER: So North
Korea is the enemy

00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:35.890
from South Korean perspective.

00:14:35.890 --> 00:14:40.720
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:14:40.720 --> 00:14:44.000
INTERPRETER: So we ignore
the people's plight,

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:46.060
their diseases,
their lack of food.

00:14:46.060 --> 00:14:48.460
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:14:48.460 --> 00:14:49.960
INTERPRETER: And
since North Korea's

00:14:49.960 --> 00:14:53.120
also at odds with
the United States.

00:14:53.120 --> 00:15:01.210
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:15:01.210 --> 00:15:02.870
INTERPRETER: So
from my perspective,

00:15:02.870 --> 00:15:05.510
the US is not really
keeping in principle

00:15:05.510 --> 00:15:07.830
to their humanitarian
principles when

00:15:07.830 --> 00:15:09.975
it comes to dealing
with North Korea.

00:15:09.975 --> 00:15:19.087
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:15:19.087 --> 00:15:20.920
INTERPRETER: So
improvements in human rights

00:15:20.920 --> 00:15:23.090
situation and
humanitarian aid, I think,

00:15:23.090 --> 00:15:26.310
can only really be improved
once the tension surrounding

00:15:26.310 --> 00:15:28.770
the Korean peninsula
can be relaxed a little.

00:15:28.770 --> 00:15:33.341
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:15:33.341 --> 00:15:34.840
INTERPRETER: So no
matter how feeble

00:15:34.840 --> 00:15:36.820
it might be, I do
my best in order

00:15:36.820 --> 00:15:39.960
to aid to the cause of peace
on the Korean peninsula.

00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:41.340
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:15:41.340 --> 00:15:43.390
INTERPRETER: To go to peace.

00:15:43.390 --> 00:15:46.394
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:15:46.394 --> 00:15:48.810
INTERPRETER: The first step
in the road to peace is first,

00:15:48.810 --> 00:15:52.250
you have to acknowledge the
difference between you and me.

00:15:52.250 --> 00:15:56.890
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:58.640
INTERPRETER: And second,
try to understand

00:15:58.640 --> 00:16:02.780
that the other might act
that way for a reason.

00:16:02.780 --> 00:16:05.240
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:16:05.240 --> 00:16:07.540
INTERPRETER: But today,
just because others do not

00:16:07.540 --> 00:16:08.835
think the way we do--

00:16:08.835 --> 00:16:13.339
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:16:13.339 --> 00:16:15.505
INTERPRETER: --we actually
paint them into a corner,

00:16:15.505 --> 00:16:19.260
saying label them as
beast, as Satan, as evil.

00:16:19.260 --> 00:16:22.696
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:16:22.696 --> 00:16:24.320
INTERPRETER: But if
you listen to them,

00:16:24.320 --> 00:16:28.490
they also think similarly about
South Korea and the United

00:16:28.490 --> 00:16:29.530
States.

00:16:29.530 --> 00:16:31.770
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:16:31.770 --> 00:16:34.450
INTERPRETER: That's why it's
difficult, the road to peace.

00:16:34.450 --> 00:16:41.095
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:16:41.095 --> 00:16:42.470
INTERPRETER: That's
well first we

00:16:42.470 --> 00:16:46.280
have to lay the foundation
of mutual understanding

00:16:46.280 --> 00:16:48.760
and acknowledgement of
each other's differences

00:16:48.760 --> 00:16:50.740
in order to arrive
at lasting peace.

00:16:50.740 --> 00:16:52.980
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:56.220
INTERPRETER: But that path is
strewn with misunderstandings.

00:16:56.220 --> 00:17:02.200
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:02.200 --> 00:17:03.700
INTERPRETER: So if
you claim that we

00:17:03.700 --> 00:17:06.609
need to acknowledge
our differences,

00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:09.079
understand their
point of view, people

00:17:09.079 --> 00:17:10.780
say you are trying
to sympathize.

00:17:10.780 --> 00:17:13.089
You are trying to
take their side.

00:17:13.089 --> 00:17:16.285
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:16.285 --> 00:17:17.910
INTERPRETER: So I
try to do what's best

00:17:17.910 --> 00:17:20.119
and what's good to
me in my thoughts,

00:17:20.119 --> 00:17:23.460
but I get criticized
from both sides.

00:17:23.460 --> 00:17:25.160
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:25.160 --> 00:17:27.796
INTERPRETER: So perhaps that's
why I live such a long life.

00:17:27.796 --> 00:17:30.824
[LAUGHTER]

00:17:30.824 --> 00:17:33.240
MALE SPEAKER: So Sunim, are
you hopeful about world peace?

00:17:38.210 --> 00:17:39.727
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:39.727 --> 00:17:41.810
INTERPRETER: I think it's
going to take some time.

00:17:41.810 --> 00:17:45.490
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:45.490 --> 00:17:48.300
INTERPRETER: Because
even just a century ago--

00:17:48.300 --> 00:17:51.820
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:51.820 --> 00:17:55.040
INTERPRETER: So we usually
lived our lives in the community

00:17:55.040 --> 00:17:56.120
that we are born in.

00:17:56.120 --> 00:17:57.200
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:57.200 --> 00:17:58.600
INTERPRETER: With
the same ethnicity.

00:17:58.600 --> 00:17:59.190
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:17:59.190 --> 00:18:00.240
INTERPRETER: With
the same religion.

00:18:00.240 --> 00:18:01.160
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:01.160 --> 00:18:02.618
INTERPRETER: With
the same culture.

00:18:02.618 --> 00:18:05.185
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:05.185 --> 00:18:06.810
INTERPRETER: So that
led us to thinking

00:18:06.810 --> 00:18:08.707
that we are always right.

00:18:08.707 --> 00:18:10.040
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:10.040 --> 00:18:12.390
INTERPRETER: But now
we are all intermixed.

00:18:12.390 --> 00:18:14.220
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:14.220 --> 00:18:16.330
INTERPRETER: And you
have that tension.

00:18:16.330 --> 00:18:19.702
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:19.702 --> 00:18:21.410
INTERPRETER: So it
takes some time for us

00:18:21.410 --> 00:18:23.990
to develop the capacity
to understand each other,

00:18:23.990 --> 00:18:25.740
acknowledge each
other's differences.

00:18:25.740 --> 00:18:27.640
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:27.640 --> 00:18:29.710
INTERPRETER: I think
we are improving.

00:18:29.710 --> 00:18:31.280
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:31.280 --> 00:18:33.340
INTERPRETER: So after
a century or so--

00:18:33.340 --> 00:18:40.590
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:40.590 --> 00:18:43.710
INTERPRETER: --I believe that
we can live together in harmony

00:18:43.710 --> 00:18:47.200
on the basis of acknowledgment
of each other's differences

00:18:47.200 --> 00:18:49.320
and understanding
of the differences.

00:18:49.320 --> 00:18:51.532
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:51.532 --> 00:18:52.990
INTERPRETER: It's
not anything else

00:18:52.990 --> 00:18:54.790
that becomes a
source of conflict.

00:18:54.790 --> 00:18:59.645
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:18:59.645 --> 00:19:01.520
INTERPRETER: So the
differences will actually

00:19:01.520 --> 00:19:04.440
be appreciated for bringing
about enrichment to our lives,

00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:06.390
rather than being a
source of conflict.

00:19:06.390 --> 00:19:09.574
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:19:09.574 --> 00:19:10.990
INTERPRETER: So
for example, there

00:19:10.990 --> 00:19:13.627
are different flowers
within the same pot.

00:19:13.627 --> 00:19:14.960
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:19:14.960 --> 00:19:16.240
INTERPRETER: Different shapes.

00:19:16.240 --> 00:19:17.020
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:19:17.020 --> 00:19:17.850
INTERPRETER: Different colors.

00:19:17.850 --> 00:19:18.760
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:19:18.760 --> 00:19:19.968
INTERPRETER: Different sizes.

00:19:19.968 --> 00:19:22.570
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:19:22.570 --> 00:19:25.320
INTERPRETER: But see, they
come together to create beauty.

00:19:25.320 --> 00:19:27.740
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:19:27.740 --> 00:19:31.804
INTERPRETER: So that's the
world that I'm dreaming about.

00:19:31.804 --> 00:19:33.220
MALE SPEAKER: So
is there anything

00:19:33.220 --> 00:19:37.280
that Googlers and Google can
help you or help world peace?

00:19:41.280 --> 00:20:01.843
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:20:01.843 --> 00:20:05.080
INTERPRETER: So it's important
for Google, as a corporation,

00:20:05.080 --> 00:20:10.030
to abide by its fiduciaries to
pursue profit at the same time.

00:20:10.030 --> 00:20:13.150
For example, allowing all of
us to use Google Maps for free.

00:20:13.150 --> 00:20:16.910
If you could allow us a lot
of spaces, a lot of areas,

00:20:16.910 --> 00:20:20.950
a lot of functions that we
could also use in common,

00:20:20.950 --> 00:20:22.860
I think that's a
great contribution.

00:20:22.860 --> 00:20:24.282
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:20:24.282 --> 00:20:26.448
INTERPRETER: Does that mean
that you won't get paid?

00:20:26.448 --> 00:20:28.540
[LAUGHTER]

00:20:28.540 --> 00:20:36.817
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:20:36.817 --> 00:20:38.650
INTERPRETER: So there's
a traditional saying

00:20:38.650 --> 00:20:41.130
that if you create a
lot of good blessings,

00:20:41.130 --> 00:20:43.190
then you will get the
blessings in return.

00:20:43.190 --> 00:20:45.650
I think you are actually
investing a lot of blessing

00:20:45.650 --> 00:20:48.531
for your own fortune
in the future.

00:20:48.531 --> 00:20:50.530
MALE SPEAKER: Now, don't
be shy to ask any time.

00:20:54.110 --> 00:20:56.670
I have one more question
before I open the floor.

00:20:56.670 --> 00:20:58.600
So this time I'm going
to shift the focus

00:20:58.600 --> 00:21:00.150
to something more local.

00:21:03.030 --> 00:21:06.680
Which is, so the
problem with modern life

00:21:06.680 --> 00:21:09.320
in a modern society, especially
in the Silicon Valley,

00:21:09.320 --> 00:21:13.180
is that people feel
overwhelmed all the time.

00:21:13.180 --> 00:21:15.755
So do you have
any advice for how

00:21:15.755 --> 00:21:18.130
to address the feeling of
being overwhelmed all the time?

00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:26.771
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:26.771 --> 00:21:28.270
INTERPRETER: I'm
not sure, actually.

00:21:28.270 --> 00:21:31.422
[LAUGHTER]

00:21:31.422 --> 00:21:32.755
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:32.755 --> 00:21:37.200
INTERPRETER: Because everything
is becoming faster and faster.

00:21:37.200 --> 00:21:39.720
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:39.720 --> 00:21:42.950
INTERPRETER: So there's a
saying in Buddhist sacred text.

00:21:42.950 --> 00:21:45.410
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:45.410 --> 00:21:48.000
INTERPRETER: Say for example,
a rabbit was taking a nap,

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:50.430
then it was alerted, woke up.

00:21:50.430 --> 00:21:51.764
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:51.764 --> 00:21:53.929
INTERPRETER: It almost felt
like the sky was falling

00:21:53.929 --> 00:21:55.090
and the earth was shaking.

00:21:55.090 --> 00:21:56.580
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:56.580 --> 00:21:58.079
INTERPRETER: And
it started running.

00:21:58.079 --> 00:21:59.710
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:21:59.710 --> 00:22:01.943
INTERPRETER: So
on the [INAUDIBLE]

00:22:01.943 --> 00:22:05.720
a deer was asking the rabbit,
where are you running?

00:22:05.720 --> 00:22:07.720
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:07.720 --> 00:22:10.447
INTERPRETER: And the rabbit
said, the sky's falling.

00:22:10.447 --> 00:22:11.780
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:11.780 --> 00:22:13.400
INTERPRETER: And the
deer asked, really?

00:22:13.400 --> 00:22:14.620
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:14.620 --> 00:22:16.661
INTERPRETER: And so the
deer followed the rabbit.

00:22:16.661 --> 00:22:18.089
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:18.089 --> 00:22:20.630
INTERPRETER: So you know, the
deer wasn't convinced at first,

00:22:20.630 --> 00:22:22.120
but he started
following the rabbit.

00:22:22.120 --> 00:22:23.453
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:23.453 --> 00:22:24.710
INTERPRETER: And other deers.

00:22:24.710 --> 00:22:26.194
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:26.194 --> 00:22:28.110
INTERPRETER: So all the
animals in the forest,

00:22:28.110 --> 00:22:30.900
you know, they actually competed
each other, raced each other.

00:22:30.900 --> 00:22:33.180
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:33.180 --> 00:22:35.230
INTERPRETER: One might
be ahead of each other,

00:22:35.230 --> 00:22:36.630
but they traded places.

00:22:36.630 --> 00:22:38.177
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:38.177 --> 00:22:39.760
INTERPRETER: Because
everybody thought

00:22:39.760 --> 00:22:42.051
they needed to run away as
soon as possible, as quickly

00:22:42.051 --> 00:22:43.230
as possible to live.

00:22:43.230 --> 00:22:48.030
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:48.030 --> 00:22:50.370
INTERPRETER: But a tall
cliff was waiting for them

00:22:50.370 --> 00:22:51.787
at the edge of the forest.

00:22:51.787 --> 00:22:53.120
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:22:53.120 --> 00:22:56.252
INTERPRETER: No one knew about
the existence of the cliff.

00:22:56.252 --> 00:23:02.709
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:02.709 --> 00:23:05.250
INTERPRETER: So they say, a lion
is watching this from above,

00:23:05.250 --> 00:23:07.560
and roared.

00:23:07.560 --> 00:23:09.812
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:09.812 --> 00:23:11.770
INTERPRETER: So all the
animals were frightened

00:23:11.770 --> 00:23:14.890
and they stopped.

00:23:14.890 --> 00:23:16.450
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:16.450 --> 00:23:18.700
INTERPRETER: So he asked the
cow, where are you going?

00:23:18.700 --> 00:23:19.240
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:19.240 --> 00:23:20.720
INTERPRETER: And the
cow said, I don't know.

00:23:20.720 --> 00:23:21.740
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:21.740 --> 00:23:22.480
INTERPRETER: Why
were you running?

00:23:22.480 --> 00:23:23.420
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:23.420 --> 00:23:25.250
INTERPRETER: Because
the horse was running.

00:23:25.250 --> 00:23:26.610
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:26.610 --> 00:23:27.900
INTERPRETER: To the horse,
why are you running?

00:23:27.900 --> 00:23:28.860
He said he didn't know, either.

00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:29.480
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:29.480 --> 00:23:30.410
INTERPRETER: Why
were you running?

00:23:30.410 --> 00:23:31.350
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:31.350 --> 00:23:32.720
INTERPRETER: Because
the sheep was running.

00:23:32.720 --> 00:23:33.900
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:33.900 --> 00:23:35.570
INTERPRETER: So he
asked all the animals.

00:23:35.570 --> 00:23:36.590
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:36.590 --> 00:23:38.400
INTERPRETER: He found the
original runner, the rabbit.

00:23:38.400 --> 00:23:39.190
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:39.190 --> 00:23:41.565
INTERPRETER: He said, why did
you run in the first place?

00:23:41.565 --> 00:23:44.814
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:44.814 --> 00:23:46.730
INTERPRETER: Because I
saw the sky was falling

00:23:46.730 --> 00:23:47.560
and the Earth shaking.

00:23:47.560 --> 00:23:48.890
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:48.890 --> 00:23:50.220
INTERPRETER: He said,
did you really see it?

00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:51.270
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:51.270 --> 00:23:53.260
INTERPRETER: So let's go back to
that place where you saw this.

00:23:53.260 --> 00:23:54.730
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:23:54.730 --> 00:23:56.313
INTERPRETER: They
go back to the place

00:23:56.313 --> 00:23:58.042
where the rabbit
was having a nap.

00:23:58.042 --> 00:24:00.010
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:00.010 --> 00:24:03.080
INTERPRETER: So he was
sleeping under an acorn tree.

00:24:03.080 --> 00:24:05.544
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:05.544 --> 00:24:07.460
INTERPRETER: So when an
acorn fell next to him

00:24:07.460 --> 00:24:10.050
while he was taking a nap,
that's what frightened him.

00:24:10.050 --> 00:24:11.530
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:11.530 --> 00:24:16.880
INTERPRETER: So they said this
was a happening, of sorts.

00:24:16.880 --> 00:24:18.780
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:18.780 --> 00:24:21.660
INTERPRETER: So perhaps that
explains where we are today.

00:24:21.660 --> 00:24:23.880
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:23.880 --> 00:24:27.860
INTERPRETER: So we are always
racing, but where are we going?

00:24:27.860 --> 00:24:30.260
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:30.260 --> 00:24:33.740
INTERPRETER: So I want to ask
you back the same question.

00:24:33.740 --> 00:24:35.556
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:35.556 --> 00:24:37.180
INTERPRETER: The
reason for you to run.

00:24:37.180 --> 00:24:38.800
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:38.800 --> 00:24:40.720
INTERPRETER: Is it because
of the money you get paid?

00:24:40.720 --> 00:24:41.960
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:41.960 --> 00:24:43.418
INTERPRETER: Is it
because you have

00:24:43.418 --> 00:24:44.775
to contribute to growing Google?

00:24:44.775 --> 00:24:46.870
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:46.870 --> 00:24:47.970
INTERPRETER: Is it really?

00:24:47.970 --> 00:24:50.670
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:50.670 --> 00:24:52.510
INTERPRETER: Why do you
have to run so fast?

00:24:52.510 --> 00:24:53.843
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:53.843 --> 00:24:57.487
INTERPRETER: I think it's time
for us to kind of review that.

00:24:57.487 --> 00:24:58.820
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:24:58.820 --> 00:25:00.070
INTERPRETER: And to
tell you this first--

00:25:00.070 --> 00:25:01.190
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:01.190 --> 00:25:02.440
INTERPRETER: And one more--

00:25:05.500 --> 00:25:08.130
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:08.130 --> 00:25:10.930
INTERPRETER: It is greed that
actually leads to anxiety.

00:25:10.930 --> 00:25:13.204
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:13.204 --> 00:25:15.120
INTERPRETER: Just because
you want to run fast

00:25:15.120 --> 00:25:17.700
doesn't necessarily
mean you run fast.

00:25:17.700 --> 00:25:19.370
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:19.370 --> 00:25:21.227
INTERPRETER: But we
always want to run fast.

00:25:21.227 --> 00:25:22.560
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:22.560 --> 00:25:24.880
INTERPRETER: But our
bodies do not agree.

00:25:24.880 --> 00:25:26.780
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:26.780 --> 00:25:28.670
INTERPRETER: That's why
it's so tough on us.

00:25:28.670 --> 00:25:30.216
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:30.216 --> 00:25:32.090
INTERPRETER: That's why
it's important for us

00:25:32.090 --> 00:25:34.290
to kind of stabilize our mind.

00:25:34.290 --> 00:25:36.336
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:36.336 --> 00:25:37.710
INTERPRETER:
Instead of being too

00:25:37.710 --> 00:25:40.170
obsessed over
wanting to run fast.

00:25:40.170 --> 00:25:42.070
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:42.070 --> 00:25:44.340
INTERPRETER: And start
thinking, growing the capacity

00:25:44.340 --> 00:25:45.470
to run fast.

00:25:45.470 --> 00:25:47.820
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:47.820 --> 00:25:50.020
INTERPRETER: But you
know, in modern world,

00:25:50.020 --> 00:25:53.220
we usually want
to run fast first.

00:25:53.220 --> 00:25:54.810
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:54.810 --> 00:25:56.080
INTERPRETER: That's
why we feel anxious.

00:25:56.080 --> 00:25:56.980
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:25:56.980 --> 00:25:58.354
INTERPRETER: And
we feel nervous.

00:25:58.354 --> 00:26:01.890
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:26:01.890 --> 00:26:03.520
INTERPRETER: And we
always are worried

00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:05.061
that somebody else
is running faster.

00:26:05.061 --> 00:26:08.020
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:26:08.020 --> 00:26:09.750
INTERPRETER: And I
think type of anxiety

00:26:09.750 --> 00:26:12.650
we are fully capable
of overcoming.

00:26:12.650 --> 00:26:15.400
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:26:15.400 --> 00:26:18.250
INTERPRETER: So I just wanted
to speak to you about that.

00:26:18.250 --> 00:26:20.940
MALE SPEAKER: So the moral of
the story is steel the mind

00:26:20.940 --> 00:26:22.861
and never trust
a talking rabbit.

