dangerous human addictions

00:26:48.370 --> 00:26:54.280
today are heroin, carbohydrates,
and a monthly salary.

00:26:54.280 --> 00:26:56.100
His name is Nassim Taleb.

00:26:56.100 --> 00:26:58.080
He's Doctor Doom.

00:26:58.080 --> 00:27:02.250
So my question to you is most
of us here have at least two

00:27:02.250 --> 00:27:07.560
out of those three addictions,
definitely the monthly salary.

00:27:07.560 --> 00:27:09.840
And every day I ask
myself the question

00:27:09.840 --> 00:27:12.640
of what is the
purpose of humans?

00:27:12.640 --> 00:27:15.530
So as a human, what
should be a noble purpose

00:27:15.530 --> 00:27:16.340
that should pursue?

00:27:21.580 --> 00:27:23.140
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:23.140 --> 00:27:26.530
INTERPRETER: Do we
need to have a purpose?

00:27:26.530 --> 00:27:29.724
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:29.724 --> 00:27:31.140
INTERPRETER: Do
you think that you

00:27:31.140 --> 00:27:33.030
need a purpose in your life?

00:27:33.030 --> 00:27:34.660
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:34.660 --> 00:27:37.160
INTERPRETER: Does a
squirrel have a purpose?

00:27:37.160 --> 00:27:39.000
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:39.000 --> 00:27:40.570
INTERPRETER: Do
deers in the hills,

00:27:40.570 --> 00:27:42.207
do they have a purpose
in their lives?

00:27:42.207 --> 00:27:43.540
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:43.540 --> 00:27:45.890
INTERPRETER: They just live.

00:27:45.890 --> 00:27:47.620
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:47.620 --> 00:27:50.420
INTERPRETER: So human beings
are not that different.

00:27:50.420 --> 00:27:52.570
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:27:52.570 --> 00:27:54.650
INTERPRETER: So meanings,
or sense of purpose,

00:27:54.650 --> 00:27:57.710
is an artifact
created by our mind.

00:27:57.710 --> 00:28:00.295
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:00.295 --> 00:28:02.670
INTERPRETER: So basically you
create the sense of purpose

00:28:02.670 --> 00:28:05.000
that you created,
and then you are

00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:07.280
imprisoned by the
sense of purpose.

00:28:07.280 --> 00:28:08.662
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:08.662 --> 00:28:10.370
INTERPRETER: So you
need to actually gain

00:28:10.370 --> 00:28:13.340
an insight into that.

00:28:13.340 --> 00:28:15.940
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:15.940 --> 00:28:19.920
INTERPRETER: So you have to be
able to look into your mind.

00:28:19.920 --> 00:28:21.384
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:21.384 --> 00:28:23.300
INTERPRETER: Because
even though you might not

00:28:23.300 --> 00:28:24.787
have a specific purpose--

00:28:24.787 --> 00:28:26.120
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:26.120 --> 00:28:28.140
INTERPRETER: --if you just
start living out your days--

00:28:28.140 --> 00:28:29.473
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:29.473 --> 00:28:31.120
INTERPRETER: --while
you are living--

00:28:31.120 --> 00:28:32.453
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:32.453 --> 00:28:34.077
INTERPRETER: --how do you live?

00:28:34.077 --> 00:28:35.410
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:35.410 --> 00:28:36.950
INTERPRETER: If you
observe people--

00:28:36.950 --> 00:28:38.420
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:38.420 --> 00:28:40.990
INTERPRETER: They live in
the midst of suffering.

00:28:40.990 --> 00:28:43.140
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:45.760
INTERPRETER: They live in the
midst of anxiety, nervousness.

00:28:45.760 --> 00:28:47.105
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:47.105 --> 00:28:49.030
INTERPRETER: They
live under stress.

00:28:49.030 --> 00:28:51.119
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:51.119 --> 00:28:52.660
INTERPRETER: But
then there are those

00:28:52.660 --> 00:28:55.910
who actually live freer and
happier than the rest of us.

00:28:55.910 --> 00:28:57.527
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:28:57.527 --> 00:28:59.360
INTERPRETER: So a lot
of people think this--

00:28:59.360 --> 00:29:01.090
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:01.090 --> 00:29:02.965
INTERPRETER: That if
you have a lot of money,

00:29:02.965 --> 00:29:04.147
you'll be freer and happier.

00:29:04.147 --> 00:29:05.480
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:05.480 --> 00:29:07.340
INTERPRETER: If you
have a high status,

00:29:07.340 --> 00:29:10.207
you'll be more free and happier.

00:29:10.207 --> 00:29:11.540
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:11.540 --> 00:29:13.123
INTERPRETER: It
almost looks that way.

00:29:13.123 --> 00:29:16.260
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:16.260 --> 00:29:18.460
INTERPRETER: But then is
people with a lot of money

00:29:18.460 --> 00:29:21.280
and high position, are they
really freer and happier?

00:29:21.280 --> 00:29:23.845
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:23.845 --> 00:29:25.970
INTERPRETER: So I don't
know how many people you've

00:29:25.970 --> 00:29:27.580
encountered in your life so far.

00:29:27.580 --> 00:29:29.087
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:29.087 --> 00:29:31.170
INTERPRETER: But I have
met a lot of those people.

00:29:31.170 --> 00:29:32.280
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:32.280 --> 00:29:33.930
INTERPRETER: But they
don't seem so happy.

00:29:33.930 --> 00:29:34.720
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:34.720 --> 00:29:36.261
INTERPRETER: They
don't seem so free.

00:29:36.261 --> 00:29:37.620
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:37.620 --> 00:29:41.450
INTERPRETER: In a way, they
are even more chased by things.

00:29:41.450 --> 00:29:44.784
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:44.784 --> 00:29:46.700
INTERPRETER: So what do
we have to do in order

00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:50.855
to be more authentically
happy and free?

00:29:50.855 --> 00:29:54.350
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:29:54.350 --> 00:29:56.680
INTERPRETER: So the
answers to those questions

00:29:56.680 --> 00:29:58.270
we can always explore.

00:29:58.270 --> 00:30:00.580
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:00.580 --> 00:30:02.830
INTERPRETER: So if you look
at how our minds operate--

00:30:05.897 --> 00:30:07.230
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:07.230 --> 00:30:09.250
INTERPRETER: For example--

00:30:09.250 --> 00:30:10.634
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:10.634 --> 00:30:12.175
INTERPRETER: --say
this is the stage.

00:30:12.175 --> 00:30:13.810
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:13.810 --> 00:30:16.390
INTERPRETER: Say this is a
discotheque, a night club.

00:30:16.390 --> 00:30:20.000
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:20.000 --> 00:30:22.500
INTERPRETER: For example, you
have the dancers, the audience

00:30:22.500 --> 00:30:27.140
of people who paid $100 a person
to come and dance in this club.

00:30:27.140 --> 00:30:30.675
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:30.675 --> 00:30:32.300
INTERPRETER: Then
there are the dancers

00:30:32.300 --> 00:30:35.740
that the club hires at $1,000
a night to actually dance

00:30:35.740 --> 00:30:37.530
on the stage.

00:30:37.530 --> 00:30:39.070
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:39.070 --> 00:30:42.130
INTERPRETER: So they all
dance to the same music.

00:30:42.130 --> 00:30:45.190
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:45.190 --> 00:30:47.960
INTERPRETER: But the people
who paid $100 to dance, they're

00:30:47.960 --> 00:30:49.070
having fun.

00:30:49.070 --> 00:30:51.450
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:51.450 --> 00:30:54.920
INTERPRETER: But the dancers
on the stage, they're working.

00:30:54.920 --> 00:30:56.580
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:30:56.580 --> 00:30:59.520
INTERPRETER: So the people below
stage are enjoying themselves.

00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:01.120
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:01.120 --> 00:31:03.070
INTERPRETER: So if you
say extended club hours

00:31:03.070 --> 00:31:04.225
by 30 minutes--

00:31:04.225 --> 00:31:05.854
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:05.854 --> 00:31:08.020
INTERPRETER: --the people
below stage, they love it.

00:31:08.020 --> 00:31:11.680
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:11.680 --> 00:31:15.120
INTERPRETER: The dancers on
the stage, they want overtime.

00:31:15.120 --> 00:31:16.546
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:16.546 --> 00:31:17.920
INTERPRETER: Why
such phenomenon?

00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:18.740
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:18.740 --> 00:31:20.800
INTERPRETER: They're doing
the same exact things.

00:31:20.800 --> 00:31:21.990
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:21.990 --> 00:31:24.031
INTERPRETER: So why is it
that people below stage

00:31:24.031 --> 00:31:25.010
are having fun?

00:31:25.010 --> 00:31:26.350
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:26.350 --> 00:31:28.055
INTERPRETER: And why is it
that the dancers on the stage

00:31:28.055 --> 00:31:28.720
are working?

00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:30.590
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:30.590 --> 00:31:32.660
INTERPRETER: So the only
difference is money.

00:31:32.660 --> 00:31:34.320
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:34.320 --> 00:31:36.250
INTERPRETER: So if
you pay, you have fun.

00:31:36.250 --> 00:31:38.040
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:38.040 --> 00:31:41.980
INTERPRETER: If you take
money, then you're working.

00:31:41.980 --> 00:31:43.440
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:43.440 --> 00:31:45.398
INTERPRETER: So you're
all getting paid, right?

00:31:45.398 --> 00:31:47.638
[LAUGHTER]

00:31:47.638 --> 00:31:51.200
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:51.200 --> 00:31:52.950
INTERPRETER: So that's
why you're working.

00:31:52.950 --> 00:31:54.810
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:54.810 --> 00:31:55.990
INTERPRETER: Because
I'm not getting paid.

00:31:55.990 --> 00:31:57.323
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:31:57.323 --> 00:31:59.880
INTERPRETER: I actually
have fun every single day.

00:31:59.880 --> 00:32:01.510
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:01.510 --> 00:32:04.210
INTERPRETER: That's
how your mind operates.

00:32:04.210 --> 00:32:08.450
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:08.450 --> 00:32:11.430
INTERPRETER: So being
free from labor--

00:32:11.430 --> 00:32:14.029
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:14.029 --> 00:32:15.570
INTERPRETER: So
being free from labor

00:32:15.570 --> 00:32:19.590
is not a matter of you getting
paid a lot for a short time.

00:32:19.590 --> 00:32:24.290
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:24.290 --> 00:32:27.200
INTERPRETER: It's for you
to enjoy, or make fun,

00:32:27.200 --> 00:32:28.926
out of your labor.

00:32:28.926 --> 00:32:30.472
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:30.472 --> 00:32:31.930
INTERPRETER: So
how do you do that?

00:32:31.930 --> 00:32:33.740
How do you transform
labor into fun?

00:32:33.740 --> 00:32:35.439
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:35.439 --> 00:32:36.980
INTERPRETER: That
means that you have

00:32:36.980 --> 00:32:40.320
to become the agent
of your own actions.

00:32:40.320 --> 00:32:44.360
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:44.360 --> 00:32:47.000
INTERPRETER: So when
you pay money to dance,

00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:49.520
the money is not the purpose.

00:32:49.520 --> 00:32:51.630
You having fun is the purpose.

00:32:51.630 --> 00:32:55.440
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:32:55.440 --> 00:32:57.720
INTERPRETER: But if
you get paid to dance,

00:32:57.720 --> 00:33:00.020
then dancing is not the purpose.

00:33:00.020 --> 00:33:02.670
The money is the purpose.

00:33:02.670 --> 00:33:04.094
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:04.094 --> 00:33:05.760
INTERPRETER: So you
are actually selling

00:33:05.760 --> 00:33:08.555
your professional dancing
abilities for money.

00:33:08.555 --> 00:33:10.470
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:10.470 --> 00:33:13.547
INTERPRETER: Then you become
enslaved to that transaction.

00:33:13.547 --> 00:33:14.880
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:14.880 --> 00:33:16.640
INTERPRETER: That's
why it's tough.

00:33:16.640 --> 00:33:18.592
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:18.592 --> 00:33:20.550
INTERPRETER: So if you
look at those principles

00:33:20.550 --> 00:33:22.260
that move our minds--

00:33:22.260 --> 00:33:24.484
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:24.484 --> 00:33:26.650
INTERPRETER: --then you are
able to diagnose at what

00:33:26.650 --> 00:33:29.090
areas and what times
you feel happy.

00:33:29.090 --> 00:33:31.359
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:31.359 --> 00:33:32.900
INTERPRETER: We
usually think that we

00:33:32.900 --> 00:33:35.197
feel we are pleased
when we receive help--

00:33:35.197 --> 00:33:36.530
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:36.530 --> 00:33:37.905
INTERPRETER: --but
that's not so.

00:33:37.905 --> 00:33:40.224
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:40.224 --> 00:33:41.640
INTERPRETER: Because
that actually

00:33:41.640 --> 00:33:44.160
is a path to enslaving yourself.

00:33:44.160 --> 00:33:50.350
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:50.350 --> 00:33:52.100
INTERPRETER: So I
encourage you to examine

00:33:52.100 --> 00:33:54.340
how your mind operates--

00:33:54.340 --> 00:33:56.000
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:57.625
INTERPRETER: --so
that you can actually

00:33:57.625 --> 00:33:59.920
bring more enjoyment
or fun to your work.

00:33:59.920 --> 00:34:01.386
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:34:01.386 --> 00:34:03.010
INTERPRETER: And to
your life, as well.

00:34:03.010 --> 00:34:05.969
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:34:05.969 --> 00:34:07.760
INTERPRETER: It's not
important whether you

00:34:07.760 --> 00:34:10.010
die today or the next day.

00:34:10.010 --> 00:34:11.947
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:34:11.947 --> 00:34:14.280
INTERPRETER: Because you need
to be happy today in order

00:34:14.280 --> 00:34:16.056
to make your next
life happy, as well.

00:34:16.056 --> 00:34:17.389
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:34:17.389 --> 00:34:19.820
INTERPRETER: So no one can
prove that the next life exists

00:34:19.820 --> 00:34:22.302
or not, of course.

00:34:22.302 --> 00:34:25.364
MALE SPEAKER: If it exists,
you'll speak English.

00:34:25.364 --> 00:34:30.237
[LAUGHTER]

00:34:30.237 --> 00:34:31.570
POMNYUN SUNIM: [SPEAKING KOREAN]

00:34:31.570 --> 00:34:33.611
INTERPRETER: Do you have
any follow up questions?

00:34:35.480 --> 00:34:37.964
MALE SPEAKER: Sunim,
that's a beautiful answer.

00:34:37.964 --> 00:34:39.380
Oh by the way, I
do have an answer

00:34:39.380 --> 00:34:43.540
for that question, what
is the meaning of life.

00:34:43.540 --> 00:34:48.309
The meaning of life is not.

